President Trump met with the National Sheriffs' Association in the Roosevelt Room of the White House. During the meeting, the President expressed his support for law enforcement and discussed issues such as the opioid epidemic, border security, terrorism, and crime. He also mentioned his frustration with delays in the approval of his Cabinet nominees. The sheriffs in attendance thanked the President for his support and discussed their concerns about drug addiction, mental health, and asset forfeiture. The meeting concluded with the President receiving a sculpture from the National Sheriffs' Association.